title: Print, "Design for a Knife Handle Showing Prudence", 1600–75
markings: Verso: stamped with an ovoid topped by a royal crown and showing crossing diagnoal lines, as in 1946-13-1.
provenance: Purchase in memory of Mrs. A. Murray Young
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of Mrs. A. Murray Young
description: Prudence is shown with a snake in an ovoid. A heart is depicted in a medalion above and two clasped hands are shown beneath the ovoid. A candelabra ornament motif sprouts from an urn at the bottom.

exhibitions.title: Feeding Desire: Design and the Tools of the Table, 1500-2005
